tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated creatinine, which may indicate reduced renal function. Glucose and HbA1c are within target ranges, suggesting good glycemic control. Electrolytes, urea, and calcium are normal. Recommend clinical correlation for renal function and consideration of repeat or further renal assessment if not previously evaluated.
